<h3 style = "font-weight: bold"> Sprint Completed Stories </h3>
<ul type = "1">
	<li> Homepage is reachable</li>
	<li> Homepage has a title</li>
	<li> Homepage has a header</li>
	<li> Homepage has a footer</li>
	<li> Homepage ahs a link to the about page in footer</li>
	<li> Homepage has a link to the home page in footer</li>
	<li> Homepage has your team logo</li>
	<li> Homepage has a link to the new event page</li>
	<li> Homepage has a list of events</li>
	<li> Homepage each event links to a "detail" page</li>
	<li> Homepage each event shows its time</li>
	<li> Homepage has background image</li>
	<li> Homepage header font size is bigger than body</li>
</ul>
	
<h3 style = "font-weight: bold"> Stories initially planned Sprint 1 are moved to Sprint 2 </h3>	
<ul type = "1" start ="14">
	<li> Homepage title font size is bigger than header </li>
	<li> Homepage uses bootstrap</li>
	<li> Homepage has borders</li>
	<li> Homepage search Bar</li>
</ul>

<h3 style = "font-weight: bold"> We defined the core aspects of the project as follows</h3>
<ul>
	<li> The entire project will be structured around 4 sprints</li>
	<li> Sprints will be on a weekly basis (7 days) from Friday to Thursday</li>
	<li> The team will meet on Thursday for a 1h sprint retrospective followed by 1h sprint planning</li>
    <li> Trello will be used as main project management tool</li>
    <li> Each week a different team member will be the scrum master</li>
    <li> The scrum master is responsible for ensuring the progress in the dev team as well as preparing the weekly status reports</li>
</ul>

<h3 style =" font-weight: bold"> First sprint planning (Oct. 26)</h3>
<ul>
	<li> We analyzed the project and defined our stories based on the provided grading code</li>
    <li> We ordered the stories by size and assigned respective amounts of story points</li>
    <li> We allocated all stories to respective sprints to finalize the project outline (see Appendix)</li>
    <li> We defined the core aspects of the project (see above)</li>
    <li> We included all stories into our project management tool (Trello)</li>
    <li> We invited Professor Jensen to our story board on Trello</li>
</ul>

<h3 style = "font-weight: bold"> Sprint (Oct.26 - Nov.1)</h3>
<p> The first sprint was very challenging and it took us a while to get our application deployed on heroku. Once we had our code online and working, we started making all changes we planned for sprint 1. Visit our page at: <a href = "https://glacial-badlands-11667.herokuapp.com/"> https://glacial-badlands-11667.herokuapp.com/ </a></p>

<p style = "text-decoration: underline"> Challenges:</p>
<ul>
	<li> Some aspects such as using bootstrap were too challenging for the first sprint (9/50 story points were unsolved), and we will definitely need support in office hours during sprint 2.</li>
    <li> Our logo and our background image worked in the Cloud9 environment, but did not show up on heroku. That’s something we are currently trying to resolve.</li>
</ul>

<h3 style = "font-weight: bold"> Sprint Retrospective (Nov.1)</h3>
<p style =" text-decoration: underline"> Product Backlog</p>
<ul>
	<li> Sprint 1:</li>
	<ul>
		<li> Homepage title font size is bigger than header</li>
		<li> Homepage uses bootstrap</li>
		<li> Homepage has borders</li>
		<li> Homepage search Bar</li>
	</ul>
	<li> New Backlog for Sprint 2 → see Appendix</li>
</ul>
<p style =" text-decoration: underline"> Goals for next week</p>
<ul>
	<li> Finish 9 story points from sprint 1</li>
	<li> Finish as much as possible of the 75 story points planned for sprint 2 </li>
    <li> Resolve issues with images on heroku</li> 
</ul>
